Definition: Is a quantification of total tau protein, a biomarker for Alzheimer's disease.
The determination of the amount of the 1-42 amino acid beta amyloid protein isoform present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of YKL-40 protein present in a sample.
Synaptosomal-associated protein 25 (206 aa, ~23 kDa) is encoded by the human SNAP25 gene. This protein plays a role in vesicular transport.

Quantification of the levels of neurofilament light chain, typically in blood or cerebrospinal fluid. Used as a marker of neurodegeneration, in Alzheimer's disease, Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis, multiple sclerosis and Huntington's disease.
A visinin-like protein 1 that is encoded in the genome of human.
A neurogranin that is encoded in the genome of human.
Alpha-synuclein (140 aa, ~14 kDa) is encoded by the human SNCA gene. This protein plays a role in the modulation of presynaptic vesicle transport and release.

Feature: Granulocyte Colony Stimulating Factor (G-GCSF) in CSF
Definition: Granulocyte colony-stimulating factor (207 aa, ~22 kDa) is encoded by the human CSF3 gene. This protein is involved in the regulation of the production, differentiation, and function of granulocytes.
Interleukin-15 (162 aa, ~18 kDa) is encoded by the human IL15 gene. This protein plays a role in the regulation of both proliferation and activation of both T-cells and natural killer cells.
Interleukin-8 (99 aa, ~11 kDa) is encoded by the human CXCL8 gene. This protein is involved in chemotaxis and neutrophil activation.

Feature: Vascular Endothelial Growth Factor (VEGF) in CSF
Definition: The determination of the amount of vascular epithelial growth factor present in a sample.

Feature: Triggering Receptor Expressed on Myeloid Cells 2 (TREM2) in CSF
Definition: Triggering receptor expressed on myeloid cells 2 (230 aa, ~25 kDa) is encoded by the human TREM2 gene. This protein plays a role in macrophage and dendritic cell immune responses.
